<br>
I've been trying to get the Band of Tunare (which I'm beginning to believe doesn't exist, in spite of Allakhazam's entry on it) for some time.  Every time I'm in Qeynos, I hit the Aqueducts once or twice to whack Ronn Castekin, a skeleton who pops up there near the Bait Masterson (or whatever) fishing site.<br>
<br>
Ronn was very green to me when I started doin this at 10th level, and even greener when I whacked him at 15th.  The note he drops for you to give to Merona, his sister in Surefall Glade, is a Lore item.  Every time I whacked him, he dropped the note.  (And every time I turned it in to Merona, I got No-Rent bread or No-rent bandages.  Thanks, Merona.)<br>
<br>
 Shouldn't it be affected by the Trivial Loot Code?  I thought the TLC applied to Magic, (formerly) No-drop, and Lore items.  Does it just apply to Magic &amp; formerly No-Drop items?<br>
<br>
Does anyone have any similar puzzles?<br>
<br>
Lasgalen <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urobingoodfellow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robin Goodfellow</A> at: 12/23/01 10:04:41 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufalconeroftunare.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Falconer of Tunare</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/24/01 5:11:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=949.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: TLC puzzler: Merona &amp; Ronn Castekin</span><hr size=1> As far as I know Ronn is merely starting in his life of undeath being only of the first season. It seems quite likely that the powers the be have left him exempt from the TLC to make this quest easier. <p><center><img src="http://members.aol.com/jimturner99/gyrhawk"></center> <b><center>Gyrhawk - Tunare's Falconer</center></b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urobingoodfellow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robin Goodfellow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/1/02 3:03:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=949.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: TLC puzzler: Merona &amp; Ronn Castekin</span><hr size=1> I hate to dredge this up again, but if Ronn Castekin's note appears to be exempt from the trivial loot code, even though it should, at least in theory, be affected by it, might we expect that other quest items have been exempted from the TLC?<br>
